

What is A/B testing ?

	A/B testing, also known as split testing, is a method used to compare two version of web page, App or any user experience element to determine 
which one perform better. It is widely used in software development, marketing to " optimize " user experience and increase engagement or 
click-through rates.

Examples of A/B testing 
	1. Web Element - Testing two layouts for a landing page to see which one leads to more sign ups.
	2. E-commerce - Comparing two versions of a product page with different images or pricing displays.

Key-Benefit
	1. Data-Driven Decisions: Helps eliminate guess work by relying on measurable results.
	2. Improved User Experience: Provides insights into what users prefer.
	3. Higher ROI: Optimizes elements to maximize engagement or conversions.